{
  "text": "Modeling of multicellular systems requires methods that go beyond the standard repertoire of model formalisms in systems biology [CITATION_1] . Cells must typically be modeled as discrete interacting entities, sometimes as motile objects, possibly even with articulated 3D cell shapes. Morpheus provides methods to define cell-based models of interactions between discrete cells, spatially represented as point-like objects or with explicit 2D/3D cell shapes. Cell motility, adhesion and biophysical *To whom correspondence should be addressed. y The authors wish it to be known that, in their opinion, the first two authors should be regarded as Joint First Authors. (5) batch processing constraints can be added using the cellular Potts model (CPM) framework [CITATION_2] .",
